headlines.description: — Miles Bridges had 20 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists and the Charlotte Hornets beat the Indiana Pacers 111-102 on Monday night to improve to 2-0 since the arrival of five new players via trade.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bridges and Charlotte's newcomers lead Hornets past Pacers for 2nd straight win, 111-102

headlines.description: — Buddy Hield is still getting used to his new surroundings. He looked much more settled in on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buddy Hield scores 24 as 76ers end Cavaliers' 9-game winning streak with 123-121 victory

headlines.description: — Ayo Dosunmu had a career-high 29 points and added seven assists to help the Chicago Bulls post a season-high score and beat the Atlanta Hawks 136-126 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ayo Dosunmu scores 29, Bulls post season high in points to beat Hawks 136-126

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Toronto Raptors

headlines.description: — Victor Wembanyama had 27 points, 14 rebounds and a career-high 10 blocks in his second triple-double, Devin Vassell added 25 points and the San Antonio Spurs snapped a seven-game losing streak by routing the Toronto Raptors 122-99 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wembanyama has career-high 10 blocks in triple-double, Spurs beat Raptors to snap 7-game skid

events.name: New York Knicks at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — The Houston Rockets got a win after a call referees said was wrong.
headlines.shortLinkText: Holiday's two free throws after foul by Brunson give Rockets 105-103 victory over Knicks

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Herbert Jones scored 17 points and Brandon Ingram finished with 16 points including a pair of late buckets as the New Orleans Pelicans held on to defeat Memphis 96-87 on Monday night, sending the Grizzlies to their ninth straight loss.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herbert Jones has 17 points, Brandon Ingram adds 16 as Pelicans hold on to beat Grizzlies 96-87

headlines.description: — The Milwaukee Bucks believed their defense was improving, even as they struggled to win games immediately after new coach Doc Rivers’ arrival.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo posts 36 points, 18 rebounds, Bucks flex defensive muscle in 112-95 win over Nuggets

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had his 10th triple-double of the season despite missing five minutes of action after taking a charge and helped rally the Dallas Mavericks to a 112-104 win over the Washington Wizards on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic records 10th triple-double of the season, leads Mavericks past Wizards 112-104

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Utah Jazz

headlines.description: — Klay Thompson scored 26 points, Stephen Curry made five 3-pointers in the fourth quarter and had 25 and the Golden State Warriors beat the Utah Jazz 129-107 on Monday night without coach Steve Kerr.
headlines.shortLinkText: Thompson scores 26, Curry has five 3s in the 4th as Warriors beat Jazz 129-107 without Kerr

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns scored 24 points, Anthony Edwards added 23 and the Minnesota Timberwolves pulled away in the second half for a 121-100 victory over the Los Angeles Clippers on Monday night in a matchup of two of the top teams in the Western...
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns, Edwards help Timberwolves rally in second half for 121-100 victory over Clippers
